**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 71/100**

Executive summary — Altria has made measurable, near-term progress adopting sustainable technologies (notably a large renewable Virtual Power Purchase Agreement), set and validated ambitious science‑based targets, and delivered specific water‑reclamation and supplier/sourcing programs. However, its sustainable‑technology activity is concentrated in energy procurement, supplier engagement, packaging/materials exploration and operational efficiency rather than broad, proprietary low‑carbon manufacturing or breakthrough technology platforms. Against large global peer programs (PMI, BAT, Imperial) Altria is a strong performer in the U.S. tobacco sector but not the clear technology leader worldwide. Key recent examples: the Inertia Wind VPPA (operational Jan 2023) that supplies ~400,000 MWh/year and is estimated to avoid ~283,000 tCO2e/year; SBTi‑validated 2030 targets and a 2050 net‑zero commitment; 2024 water‑reclamation metrics (Philip Morris USA wetlands ~237M gallons treated; ~122M gallons reused); acquisitions and partnerships (NJOY acquisition, JV with Japan Tobacco Group for heated tobacco). See sources below for the primary references ([altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEQxiTWVhgC-o8d3mzKc_-fc3kmmeBhKgSagkmeodr9zHf3u7pzZxIJxhz9YUOHsucvtkG6soAWH1H7-S0IgXPvFDkliELHs_ak8On_Rdu9YN_QNdGKGsx7Wv6CxkngoYZJCwUA5UzaUX6jx-LPwR8QMbSw9EHXmhKLLEv6-37J7X_I6rexuux3bIzCF9IIuozSvBNoHOrGYCY4L5mg7jGfTsMjnVoO5OTII7NHiI6es4C-91LOyab-UcN5f8x14LTJRs9T8MUg4tHdkPX37CSyfOpI3eGYbDKobx-65DSJ4mpU4RzKISW0u4BDDsiyzHPW0_0=); [tobaccoreporter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHCXZ4dMO6JDiv68kSghuMAN7kKwuAp5Le8iuHITGG5FNU8bmOEAgysCj4EdZ3yUbXSEefOx8gfy4cnFvFTRsTmMDN6cuYE_UkGHLwS9J1t0rdsgvP7rvkprHMvoYjRQ0LwBsCudj1JOJKcNi-tNYlKq4NmJUCKmBMgYbFWEh8yyuRKxltrRuem8BojdPVt-AM=); [altria SBTi/targets](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHoUif25fD91ASgobn-wOCpGk1ogp9GkLXbNGexHVO38gDf20g7Iy3abeToHC