Detailed findings by research area (2022–2025 examples and metrics)

Technology Adoption (what specific sustainable technologies has Altria implemented?)
- Large-scale renewable electricity procurement via a Virtual Power Purchase Agreement (VPPA) tied to the Inertia Wind Energy Center (Texas). Altria’s contracted portion is reported at ~400,000 MWh/year (operational Jan 2023) and is estimated to reduce ~283,000 metric tons CO2e annually while supplying renewable electricity credits to address 100% of its purchased U.S. electricity demand ([altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEQxiTWVhgC-o8d3mzKc_-fc3kmmeBhKgSagkmeodr9zHf3u7pzZxIJxhz9YUOHsucvtkG6soAWH1H7-S0IgXPvFDkliELHs_ak8On_Rdu9YN_QNdGKGsx7Wv6CxkngoYZJCwUA5UzaUX6jx-LPwR8QMbSw9EHXmhKLLEv6-37J7X_I6rexuux3bIzCF9IIuozSvBNoHOrGYCY4L5mg7jGfTsMjnVoO5OTII7NHiI6es4C-91LOyab-UcN5f8x14LTJRs9T8MUg4tHdkPX37CSyfOpI3eGYbDKobx-65DSJ4mpU4RzKISW0u4BDDsiyzHPW0_0=); [tobaccoreporter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHCXZ4dMO6JDiv68kSghuMAN7kKwuAp5Le8iuHITGG5FNU8bmOEAgysCj4EdZ3yUbXSEefOx8gfy4cnFvFTRsTmMDN6cuYE_UkGHLwS9J1t0rdsgvP7rvkprHMvoYjRQ0LwBsCudj1JOJKcNi-tNYlKq4NmJUCKmBMgYbFWEh8yyuRKxltrRuem8BojdPVt-AM=); [energychoicematters](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPfeqTSV6gX4xVNXoVM4SbmGRxMxQl-1XUbbFT6v4AMX81eZjWwD8Mi0PCto52vHDOnaVm2ueSj_IYxFyV6ti3qpIyg5pOPndJRMMr6e-PU2xF1HUI68uJb97s0it19qhTiFX6JjnJjYn8xSBCIPuabamX2w==)).  
- Energy & emissions management programs with SBTi‑aligned targets (see next sections) and market‑based reporting; TCFD risk assessment and disclosures to integrate climate risk into operations ([altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEBtJTq8IvFER_wEuWzRIEoeVJTzCopNYIvWQCk2doPuRqM8APLTvcUgq2oEbjQY9bjo-9ZqGyIh129bpnTJ5pe4eF8HV9SMn9rkXDEigK6Llx4RRf3MR1-7Ios4Da-mR5yIkqV1qX5v6UAbHu-1uxlDZ9uqgJ0m5aLnx9GyMBtwBamKijMPWk=); [altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEL1mCL85qGJNG5OQN5WOJl-CPdysO71FDNbVHjCOdg2HFu9BvTWyoGST7ZQ8bui7imKnCA71X6VOoAy1grXEKIDrxEdxs1KXeGLBkgJSPg97IaDBM7crX6TYhQ8Y0yMYoJicxP2_ZzBw5lz7iL_O30fHIIXBP6yXeajw8jGbk5-Z7z-S1FEA==)).  
- Water‑reclamation and natural treatment systems at manufacturing sites: Philip Morris USA wetlands treated ~237 million gallons and reused ~122 million gallons in 2024 via a manufacturing center water reclamation hub ([altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFcWODCZg_RWF_NoTKHb6A-QhOUZF3n_gA9qp_Na2vBrxF0g5Ew4lEVlZU62MUhqqckFYL5REhyEIZ1vGoFXGYK6Q1R-nRmXnXvQ1NeXKTDAfmLUy_Eu-_NXa4NTCk5QFbKWesfZBdWQQxoAwlnfnD3CG5NyRtTtu1QHAPstR0bh2ZDaZDa0thWB9wC94CsFvMr4RN5PBc=); [altria](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGp6G4Ms7pT46Ao4xO56j-8cDSInv7SozFqEBeuP7jsgV4zV9OHlyWhHrPfGFdXo39Om1mv3_3V2-7jynHrAcTjg40kNR6JNIpjcI7AdR2HEfmISSSDBQrt17uhdf77LMdWXNl1oK9b9U1ax_gRgZFa5meeKd_M7_x7Ttp8wawN4mS4jF7s3r_CS8OH4fwl1KIMXZACnME=)).  
