Score calculation: 18 + 16 + 17 + 13 + 7 = 71 / 100

Overall Assessment
Altria has credible, validated commitments and concrete deployments (notably the Inertia Wind VPPA and proven water‑reclamation work), plus a strengthened SBTi‑aligned targets roadmap and active supplier/sourcing programs. These put Altria solidly in the “strong performer” category for sustainable technology adoption in its sector. Its innovation strength is concentrated in product engineering, M&A and partnerships (smoke‑free product tech) rather than proprietary, large‑scale low‑carbon manufacturing technologies. To move toward top global leadership (score 85–100) Altria would need to show larger, company‑owned deployments of low‑carbon process technologies, more breakthrough R&D investments specifically targeted at decarbonizing manufacturing and logistics, and higher external recognition (e.g., top CDP/Tier ratings) for climate and forests.

